_url`)\n36:   - Extract namespace from deployment info\n37:   - Return tuple: `(metadata, endpoint, namespace)`\n38:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py`\n39:   - Verify: Raises `ValueError` if not published, returns correct tuple\n40: \n41: - [x] **T2.2** Implement `InvokeRuntime.invoke()` main method\n42:   - Call `_validate_invoke_prerequisites()` to get endpoint\n43:   - For `agentcube` provider with `AgentRuntime` CR: construct invocation URL\n44:   - Inject `session_id` into headers if present in metadata\n45:   - Route to appropriate invocation method based on provider\n46:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py`\n47:   - Verify: Correct URL construction, session header injection\n48: \n49: - [x] **T2.3** Implement `InvokeRuntime._invoke_agent_via_agentcube()`\n50:   - Async HTTP POST to endpoint with payload and headers\n51:   - Use `httpx.AsyncClient` with 60s timeout\n52:   - Parse JSON response\n53:   - Handle non-HTTP endpoints gracefully\n54:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py`\n55:   - Verify: Returns JSON response, handles errors\n56: \n57: - [x] **T2.4** Implement `InvokeRuntime._direct_http_invocation()`\n58:   - Async HTTP POST for standard K8s deployments\n59:   - Use `httpx.AsyncClient` with 60s timeout\n60:   - Return JSON response dict\n61:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py`\n62:   - Verify: Returns correct response format\n63: \n64: - [x] **T2.5** Implement fallback logic for endpoint failures\n65:   - Try agentcube invocation first, fallback to direct HTTP\n66:   - Handle invalid endpoint formats gracefully\n67:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py`\n68:   - Verify: Fallback works when primary fails\n69: \n70: ---\n71: \n72: ## Phase 3: Status Runtime Implementation ✓\n73: \n74: - [x] **T3.1** Implement `StatusRuntime.get_status()` main method\n75:   - Load metadata, check if published\n76:   - Route to provider-specific status getter\n77:   - Return consistent status dict structure\n78:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py`\n79:   - Verify: Returns correct status dict for different scenarios\n80: \n81: - [x] **T3.2** Implement `StatusRuntime._get_cr_k8s_status()` for AgentRuntime CR\n82:   - Use `AgentCubeProvider` to query CR\n83:   - Extract status from `cr_object[\"status\"]`\n84:   - Return fields: `status`, `provider`, `namespace`, `agent_name`, `agent_endpoint`, `message`\n85:   - Handle CR not found case\n86:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py`\n87:   - Verify: Returns correct CR status, handles 404\n88: \n89: - [x] **T3.3** Implement `StatusRuntime._get_k8s_status()` for standard K8s deployment\n90:   - Use `KubernetesProvider.get_agent_status()`\n91:   - Extract replica info: `replicas`, `ready_replicas`\n92:   - Return fields: `status`, `provider`, `namespace`, `deployment_name`, replica counts\n93:   - Add message for not fully ready state\n94:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py`\n95:   - Verify: Returns correct deployment status\n96: \n97: - [x] **T3.4** Implement error handling and status messages\n98:   - Return `not_published` status when agent not deployed\n99:   - Return `error` status with message on exceptions\n100:   - Return `not_found_in_k8s` when CR/deployment missing\n101:   - Return `created_no_status` when CR has no status subresource yet\n102:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/status_runtime.py`\n103:   - Verify: All error cases return appropriate status codes\n104: \n105: ---\n106: \n107: ## Phase 4: CLI Integration ✓\n108: \n109: - [x] **T4.1** Add `invoke` command to CLI with Typer\n110:   - Options: `workspace`, `payload`, `header_list`, `provider`, `verbose`\n111:   - Default payload: `\"{}\"`\n112:   - Multiple `--header` flags allowed\n113:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py`\n114:   - Verify: `agentcube invoke --help` shows all options\n115: \n116: - [x] **T4.2** Implement payload JSON parsing and validation\n117:   - Parse `payload` string as JSON early\n118:   - Exit with code 1 on invalid JSON with clear error message\n119:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py`\n120:   - Verify: Rejects invalid JSON with helpful message\n121: \n122: - [x] **T4.3** Implement header parsing and validation\n123:   - Parse `key:value` format, split on first `:`\n124:   - Validate format, reject if no colon\n125:   - Trim whitespace from key and value\n126:   - Build headers dict\n127:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py`\n128:   - Verify: Accepts valid headers, rejects invalid format\n129: \n130: - [x] **T4.4** Implement `invoke` command progress UI\n131:   - Use `rich.progress` spinner during invocation\n132:   - Display success message with JSON response\n133:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py`\n134:   - Verify: Spinner displays, output formatted clearly\n135: \n136: - [x] **T4.5** Add `status` command to CLI with Typer\n137:   - Options: `workspace`, `provider`, `verbose`\n138:   - Default provider: `\"agentcube\"`\n139:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py`\n140:   - Verify: `agentcube status --help` shows all options\n141: \n142: - [x] **T4.6** Implement `status` command progress UI\n143:   - Use `rich.progress` spinner during status fetch\n144:   - Check for `not_published` or `error` status\n145:   - Exit with code 1 and helpful message for those cases\n146:   - Display status details as key-value pairs\n147:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py`\n148:   - Verify: Clear status output, correct exit codes\n149: \n150: - [x] **T4.7** Implement consistent error handling for both commands\n151:   - Use `_handle_error()` helper with verbose traceback option\n152:   - Exit code 1 on failure\n153:   - Red error messages with context\n154:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py`\n155:   - Verify: Errors display clearly, verbose mode shows traceback\n156: \n157: ---\n158: \n159: ## Phase 5: Validation & Edge Cases\n160: \n161: - [ ] **T5.1** Validate `router_url` is present for AgentRuntime CR invocation\n162:   - Check metadata for `router_url` when provider is `agentcube`\n163:   - Raise `ValueError` with helpful message if missing\n164:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py`\n165:   - Verify: Clear error when router_url missing\n166: \n167: - [ ] **T5.2** Validate header format more strictly\n168:   - Check for empty key or value after split\n169:   - Warn about duplicate headers\n170:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py`\n171:   - Verify: Rejects `:value` or `key:` formats\n172: \n173: - [ ] **T5.3** Add timeout handling with clear error messages\n174:   - Catch `httpx.TimeoutException` separately\n175:   - Display \"Request timed out after Xs\" message\n176:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py`\n177:   - Verify: Timeout shows clear message, not stack trace\n178: \n179: - [ ] **T5.4** Validate workspace path exists before invocation\n180:   - Check `workspace_path.exists()` early\n181:   - Raise helpful error if directory missing\n182:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/cli/main.py`\n183:   - Verify: Early error for non-existent workspace\n184: \n185: - [ ] **T5.5** Handle HTTP error codes gracefully\n186:   - Catch `httpx.HTTPStatusError` with status code\n187:   - Display status code and response body\n188:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py`\n189:   - Verify: Clear error on 4xx/5xx responses\n190: \n191: - [ ] **T5.6** Log invocation details in verbose mode\n192:   - Log endpoint URL, payload size, headers (excluding sensitive)\n193:   - Log response status code and size\n194:   - File: `cmd/cli/agentcube/runtime/invoke_runtime.py`\n195:   - Verify: Debug logs appear with `--verbose`\n196: \n197: ---\n198: \n199: ## Phase 6: Testing\n200: \n201: - [ ] **T6.1** Unit test `InvokeRuntime._validate_invoke_prerequisites()`\n202:   - Test with published agent (has `agent_id`)\n203:   - Test with unpublished agent (no `agent_id`)\n204:   - Test with endpoint but no agent_id\n205:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_invoke_runtime.py`\n206:   - Verify: Correct validation, appropriate errors\n207: \n208: - [ ] **T6.2** Unit test `InvokeRuntime.invoke()` with mock HTTP\n209:   - Mock `httpx.AsyncClient.post()`\n210:   - Test session_id header injection\n211:   - Test payload passing\n212:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_invoke_runtime.py`\n213:   - Verify: Correct HTTP call, headers included\n214: \n215: - [ ] **T6.3** Unit test `InvokeRuntime._invoke_agent_via_agentcube()`\n216:   - Test successful response\n217:   - Test HTTP error response\n218:   - Test timeout handling\n219:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_invoke_runtime.py`\n220:   - Verify: Response parsing, error propagation\n221: \n222: - [ ] **T6.4** Unit test `StatusRuntime.get_status()` scenarios\n223:   - Test not_published case\n224:   - Test successful status retrieval\n225:   - Test error case\n226:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_status_runtime.py`\n227:   - Verify: Correct status dict returned\n228: \n229: - [ ] **T6.5** Unit test `StatusRuntime._get_cr_k8s_status()`\n230:   - Mock `AgentCubeProvider.get_agent_runtime()`\n231:   - Test CR with status subresource\n232:   - Test CR without status subresource\n233:   - Test CR not found\n234:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_status_runtime.py`\n235:   - Verify: Correct status extraction\n236: \n237: - [ ] **T6.6** Unit test `StatusRuntime._get_k8s_status()`\n238:   - Mock `KubernetesProvider.get_agent_status()`\n239:   - Test with ready replicas\n240:   - Test with partial ready replicas\n241:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_status_runtime.py`\n242:   - Verify: Replica counts correct\n243: \n244: - [ ] **T6.7** CLI test: `invoke` command header parsing\n245:   - Test valid headers: `--header \"Authorization: Bearer token\"`\n246:   - Test invalid headers: `--header \"invalid\"`\n247:   - Test multiple headers\n248:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_cli.py`\n249:   - Verify: Headers parsed correctly, errors on invalid\n250: \n251: - [ ] **T6.8** CLI test: `invoke` command payload parsing\n252:   - Test valid JSON: `--payload '{\"key\": \"value\"}'`\n253:   - Test invalid JSON: `--payload 'not json'`\n254:   - Test empty payload: `--payload '{}'`\n255:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_cli.py`\n256:   - Verify: JSON parsed, errors on invalid\n257: \n258: - [ ] **T6.9** CLI test: `status` command output\n259:   - Test published agent status display\n260:   - Test not_published exit code and message\n261:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/test_cli.py`\n262:   - Verify: Output format, exit codes\n263: \n264: - [ ] **T6.10** Integration test: invoke against mock server\n265:   - Use `httpx-mock` or test HTTP server\n266:   - Test full invoke flow with mocked endpoint\n267:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/integration/test_invoke_integration.py`\n268:   - Verify: End-to-end invoke works\n269: \n270: - [ ] **T6.11** Integration test: status against mock K8s\n271:   - Mock K8s API responses\n272:   - Test status retrieval flow\n273:   - File: `cmd/cli/tests/integration/test_status_integration.py`\n274:   - Verify: End-to-end status works\n275: \n276: ---\n277: \n278: ## Phase 7: Documentation & Cleanup\n279: \n280: - [ ] **T7.1** Add docstrings to all public methods\n281:   - Follow Google/NumPy style\n282:   - Document args, returns, raises\n283:   - File: `invoke_runtime.py`, `status_runtime.py`\n284:   - Verify: `help()` displays correctly\n285: \n286: - [ ] **T7.2** Add type hints to all functions\n287:   - Use `typing` module for complex types\n288:   - Ensure `mypy` passes\n289:   - File: All invoke/status related files\n290:   - Verify: Type checking passes\n291: \n292: - [ ] **T7.3** Update README with invoke/status command examples\n293:   - Show `agentcube invoke --payload '{\"message\": \"hello\"}'`\n294:   - Show `agentcube invoke --header \"Authorization: Bearer token\"`\n295:   - Show `agentcube status`\n296:   - File: `cmd/cli/README.md`\n297:   - Verify: Examples are copy-paste runnable\n298: \n299: - [ ] **T7.4** Add troubleshooting section for common errors\n300:   - Invalid payload JSON\n301:   - Invalid header format\n302:   - Agent not published\n303:   - Connection timeouts\n304:   - K8s API errors\n305:   - File: `cmd/cli/README.md` or `docs/cli/invoke-status.md`\n306:   - Verify: Clear resolutions for each error\n307: \n308: - [ ] **T7.5** Add inline comments for complex logic\n309:   - URL construction for AgentRuntime invocation\n310:   - Session ID header injection\n311:   - Status determination logic\n312:   - File: Runtime files\n313:   - Verify: Code is self-documenting\n314: \n315: ---\n316: \n317: ## Acceptance Criteria\n318: \n319: 1. ✅ `InvokeRuntime` class fully implemented with all methods\n320: 2. ✅ `StatusRuntime` class fully implemented with all methods\n321: 3. ✅ CLI `invoke` command accepts all required options\n322: 4. ✅ CLI `status` command accepts all required options\n323: 5. ✅ Header parsing validates `key:value` format\n324: 6. ✅ Payload JSON parsing validates early\n325: 7. ✅ Session ID injected from metadata when available\n326: 8. ✅ Two providers supported: `agentcube` and `k8s`\n327: 9. ✅ Status command exits with code 1 for `not_published`/`error`\n328: 10. ✅ Error handling provides clear, actionable messages\n329: 11. ⏳ Unit tests cover all runtime methods\n330: 12. ⏳ Integration tests validate end-to-end flows\n331: 13. ⏳ Documentation includes examples and troubleshooting\n332: \n333: ---\n334: \n335: **Notes:**\n336: - Stage ST-3 is marked complete: runtime classes and CLI commands are implemented\n337: - Remaining work: comprehensive testing (Phase 6) and documentation (Phase 7)\n338: - Edge case validation (Phase 5) needs implementation for router_url, timeouts, HTTP errors\n\n(End of file - total 338 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-023 — CLI invoke/status Commands Tasks\n\n**Module:** `cmd/cli`  \n**Language:** Python  \n**Size:** M  \n**Stage:** ST-3 (completed)\n\n---\n\n## Phase 1: Foundation & Models ✓\n\n- [x] **T1